text: William Leslie McJannet (born 2 August 1961) is a Scottish former footballer who made 193 appearances in the Football League playing as a right back for Mansfield Town, Scarborough and Darlington between 1979 and 1992. He remained with Darlington for their 1989–90 Football Conference title-winning season, and also played non-league football for clubs including King's Lynn, and Burton Albion, Matlock Town and Boston United.Harman. Alliance to Conference. pp. 122, 131.
